Source: Brazilian National Health Foundation, Technical Note [edited
<http://www.funasa.gov.br/not/not123.htm>

Yellow Fever - Brazil (Minas Gerais) - 13 Confirmed Cases
---------------------------------------------------------
The Brazilian National Health Foundation (FUNASA) has published a
technical note that confirmed a total of 13 yellow fever cases with 9
deaths up to 23 Feb 2001 in the most recent outbreak affecting rural
communities in the central-west part of Minas Gerais State, Brazil. Most
cases were male and the age varied from 20 to 51 years-old.
The technical note also report that in 1998, 1999 and 2000 there were
respectively 34, 76 and 85 reported cases of yellow fever in Brazil
distributed throughout Amazonas, Acre, Para, Roraima, Tocantins,
Goias, Distrito Federal, Mato Grosso, Sao Paulo and Bahia States. In
the Minas Gerais State, the last outbreak was reported in 1994.
FUNASA has intensified the yellow fever vaccination among the population
near the affected areas. Since 1998, 40 million people has been
vaccinated against yellow fever through immunization campaigns done in
the susceptible areas.
--
